This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3405

1.Normal mode
    ;;      Exit without saving
    ,,      Save and exit
    mm   to compile and debug
2.Insert mode
    mm      return Normal mode
    <Alt-j>  Down
    <Alt-k> Up
    <Alt-h> Left
    <Alt-l>  Right
3.When writing c, cpp ,... code, the code is automatically formatted
    For example:   If you input a==3;
    auto.vim                             a  ==  3;
4.Both ruby , c, cpp, python,shell,perl code, F2 key or "mm" to compile and debug

modify from this: 
http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3341

